Class MovePool

java.lang.Object
engine.forBoard.MovePool
public final class MovePool extends Object
The MovePool class provides object pooling for Move instances to reduce garbage collection pressure and improve performance during chess engine search operations. Each Move type has its own dedicated pool for efficient reuse of objects.

Object pooling is particularly important in chess engines where millions of move objects can be created during search, causing significant garbage collection overhead. By reusing existing objects instead of continuously creating new ones, the engine can achieve better performance and reduced memory usage.

This class follows the singleton pattern with a static INSTANCE field to ensure only one pool exists throughout the application lifecycle. It provides separate pools for each concrete move type (MajorMove, MajorAttackMove, PawnMove, etc.) and maintains statistics about pool usage.

Author:
Aaron Ho

  • Constructor Details

    • MovePool

      private MovePool()
      Private constructor to enforce the singleton pattern. Initializes all move type pools with pre-allocated instances to reduce allocation during engine operation.

  • Method Details

    • initializePools

      private void initializePools()
      Initializes all move pools with pre-allocated move objects. This method populates each type-specific pool with a default number of objects (POOL_SIZE) to minimize allocations during the critical path of chess engine search operations.

      public Move.MajorMove getMajorMove(Board board, Piece pieceMoved, int destinationCoordinate)
